# Option 2: Use websocat command line tool
# ------------------------------------------
# Install: cargo install websocat
# Run: websocat ws://localhost:7376/ws/chat
#
# Option 3: Use Python
# --------------------
# Run: python test_websocket_client.py
#

###############################################
# OPENAPI SPEC TESTS
###############################################

### Get OpenAPI spec
GET {{baseUrl}}/openapi.json

# curl: curl http://localhost:7376/openapi.json

### Interactive API documentation
### Open in browser: http://localhost:7376/docs

### Alternative API docs (Scalar)
### Open in browser: http://localhost:7376/redoc

###############################################
# ERROR HANDLING TESTS
###############################################

### Test 404 error
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/nonexistent

# Should return: 404 Not Found

### Test validation error
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "invalid-email"
}

# Should return: 422 Validation Error

###############################################
# PERFORMANCE TESTS
###############################################

### Concurrent requests test
### Run this in multiple terminals
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users?limit=100

# curl: curl -w "@curl-format.txt" http://localhost:7376/api/users?limit=100

### Expected response time: < 100ms
